        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275965\">Evan Patterson</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229457-MIT-Categories.20Seminar/topic/December.2010.3A.20Evan.20Patterson's.20talk/near/219568507\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Slides for the talk are posted here: <a href=\"https://www.algebraicjulia.org/assets/slides/mit-seminar-2020/\">https://www.algebraicjulia.org/assets/slides/mit-seminar-2020/</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Just out of curiosity, how did you make these slides <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"275965\">@Evan Patterson</span> ? Looks pretty slick <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span></p>",
        "id": 219668678,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Forgy",
        "timestamp": 1607724500
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! I used <a href=\"https://github.com/piever/Remark.jl\">Remark.jl</a>, which integrates <a href=\"https://remarkjs.com\">RemarkJS</a> with <a href=\"https://github.com/JuliaDocs/Documenter.jl\">Documenter.jl</a>. TikZ diagrams are provided by TikzPictures.jl and TikzCDs.jl. This setup does a fairly good job at allowing code, code output, and math to all be integrated into a slideshow.</p>",
        "id": 219669422,
        "sender_full_name": "Evan Patterson",
        "timestamp": 1607724982
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are they on Github?</p>",
        "id": 219669623,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Forgy",
        "timestamp": 1607725163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Found it:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/AlgebraicJulia/algebraicjulia.org/tree/develop/page/_assets/slides/mit-seminar-2020\">https://github.com/AlgebraicJulia/algebraicjulia.org/tree/develop/page/_assets/slides/mit-seminar-2020</a></p>",
        "id": 219669908,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Forgy",
        "timestamp": 1607725390
